<refnamediv>
<refname>Tk_MainLoop</refname>
<refpurpose>loop for events until all windows are deleted</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv xml:id='synopsis'>
<funcsynopsis>
<funcsynopsisinfo>
#include &lt;tk.h&gt;

</funcsynopsisinfo>
<funcprototype>
<funcdef><function>Tk_MainLoop</function></funcdef>
<void/></funcprototype>

</funcsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 xml:id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para><function>Tk_MainLoop</function> is a procedure that loops repeatedly calling
<emphasis remap='B'>Tcl_DoOneEvent</emphasis>.  It returns only when there are no applications
left in this process (i.e. no main windows exist anymore).  Most
windowing applications will call <function>Tk_MainLoop</function> after
initialization; the main execution of the application will consist
entirely of callbacks invoked via <emphasis remap='B'>Tcl_DoOneEvent</emphasis>.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1 xml:id='keywords'><title>KEYWORDS</title>
<para>application, event, main loop</para>
</refsect1>
